<DocsLayout title="Skill Library">
  <h1>Skill Library</h1>
  
  <p class="lead">
    Organize, version, and share your MDZ skills effectively to build reusable skill libraries.
  </p>

  <h2>Directory Structure</h2>
  
  <p>Organize your skills in a clear hierarchy:</p>
  
  <pre><code>skills/
├── personal/
│   ├── greeting.mdz
│   └── code-review.mdz
├── team/
│   ├── project-specific.mdz
│   └── shared-workflows.mdz
└── shared/
    ├── coding/
    │   ├── typescript.mdz
    │   └── debugging.mdz
    └── communication/
        ├── email.mdz
        └── meeting-notes.mdz</code></pre>
  
  <p>This structure separates personal, team, and shared skills while grouping by domain.</p>

  <h2>Versioning Strategy</h2>
  
  <p>Use semantic versioning (SemVer) for skills:</p>
  
  <ul>
    <li><strong>MAJOR</strong> - Breaking changes to inputs, outputs, or behavior</li>
    <li><strong>MINOR</strong> - New features or enhancements, backward compatible</li>
    <li><strong>PATCH</strong> - Bug fixes and minor improvements</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p>Tag releases in git for easy reference:</p>
  
  <pre><code class="language-bash">git tag v1.2.3
git push origin v1.2.3</code></pre>
  
  <p>Include version in skill frontmatter for tracking:</p>
  
  <pre><code>---
name: greeting
version: 1.2.3
description: A friendly greeting skill
---</code></pre>

  <h2>Sharing Patterns</h2>
  
  <p>Share skills through version-controlled repositories:</p>
  
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Git Repositories</strong> - Host on GitHub, GitLab, or similar</li>
    <li><strong>Public Sharing</strong> - Open-source community skills</li>
    <li><strong>Private Sharing</strong> - Internal team or organization skills</li>
    <li><strong>Git Submodules</strong> - Include shared skills in your projects</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p>Add a shared skill library:</p>
  
  <pre><code class="language-bash">git submodule add https://github.com/user/shared-skills.git skills/shared</code></pre>
  
  <p>For distribution, consider packaging compiled skills as npm packages if needed.</p>

  <h2>Team Workflows</h2>
  
  <p>Treat skills as code with standard development practices:</p>
  
  <ul>
    <li>Use feature branches for developing new skills</li>
    <li>Require pull request reviews before merging</li>
    <li>Validate skills in CI/CD pipelines</li>
    <li>Document skill usage and examples</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p>Example GitHub Actions workflow for validation:</p>
  
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">name: Validate Skills
on: [push, pull_request]
jobs:
  validate:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
      - run: npm install -g zenmarkdown
      - run: mdz check skills/**/*.mdz</code></pre>
  
  <p>Regularly update shared submodules and test integrations.</p>
</DocsLayout>